{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871253232,"sessionID":"ses_285d35baeffenWjdb48dAJwLcJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2cdaa600180Rdk9uE2PmSWq","messageID":"msg_d7a2cc102001LUHAAQCIbUhQY6","sessionID":"ses_285d35baeffenWjdb48dAJwLcJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-57e4a7d9fe884e50ad64dcba47d7133d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal describes the design and implementation of `DockerService` as a core service module within the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The service provides a Pythonic abstraction layer over Docker SDK operations required by the CLI's `pack`, `build`, and `publish` workflows.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### DockerService Class (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n10: \n11: The `DockerService` class will encapsulate all Docker SDK interactions:\n12: \n13: - **Docker availability check**: Verify Docker daemon is running and accessible\n14: - **Image building**: Build container images from Dockerfiles with optional build arguments\n15: - **Image information retrieval**: Query image metadata (ID, size, creation time)\n16: - **Image pushing**: Authenticate and push images to container registries\n17: - **Image removal**: Clean up local images with graceful error handling\n18: \n19: **Class interface**:\n20: ```python\n21: class DockerService:\n22:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None\n23:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool\n24:     def build_image(\n25:         self,\n26:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n27:         context_path: Path,\n28:         image_name: str,\n29:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n30:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n31:     ) -> Dict[str, str]\n32:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]\n33:     def push_image(\n34:         self,\n35:         image_name: str,\n36:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n37:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n38:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n39:     ) -> Dict[str, str]\n40:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ### Method Responsibilities\n44: \n45: #### `check_docker_available()`\n46: - Attempts to connect to Docker daemon via `docker.from_env()`\n47: - Returns `True` if connection succeeds, `False` otherwise\n48: - Logs warnings when Docker is unavailable (respecting `verbose` flag)\n49: \n50: #### `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args)`\n51: - Builds image using `client.images.build()`\n52: - Streams build logs to CLI for real-time user feedback\n53: - Supports build arguments for proxy configuration\n54: - Tags image as `{image_name}:{tag}`\n55: - Returns dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n56: - Raises `RuntimeError` on build failure\n57: \n58: #### `get_image_info(image_name)`\n59: - Retrieves image metadata via `client.images.get()`\n60: - Returns dict with `id`, `repo_tags`, `size`, `created`\n61: - Uses internal `_format_size()` for human-readable size formatting\n62: - Raises `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` if image doesn't exist\n63: \n64: #### `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password)`\n65: - Logs in to registry if credentials provided via `_docker_login_sdk()`\n66: - Retags image if `registry_url` is specified via `_tag_image_sdk()`\n67: - Streams push logs to CLI\n68: - Returns dict with `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n69: - Handles authentication errors gracefully\n70: \n71: #### `remove_image(image_name)`\n72: - Removes image via `client.images.remove()`\n73: - Returns `True` on success\n74: - Logs warning and returns `False` on failure\n75: - Forces removal if image has dependent containers\n76: \n77: ## Design Considerations\n78: \n79: ### Error Handling Strategy\n80: - Wrap Docker SDK exceptions with descriptive error messages\n81: - Maintain stack traces in verbose mode for debugging\n82: - Use `RuntimeError` for unrecoverable failures (Docker unavailable, build failures)\n83: - Log warnings for non-critical issues (image removal failures)\n84: \n85: ### Logging and Verbosity\n86: - Respect `verbose` flag for detailed operation logging\n87: - Use Python standard `logging` module\n88: - Log at INFO level for normal operations, DEBUG for verbose mode\n89: - Integration with CLI's verbose flag passed from runtime classes\n90: \n91: ### Streaming Output\n92: - Stream build and push logs to CLI using generators\n93: - Provide real-time feedback to users during long-running operations\n94: - Decode Docker API log lines for display\n95: \n96: ### Registry Authentication\n97: - Support standard Docker registry authentication\n98: - Handle both Docker Hub and private registries\n99: - Store credentials securely via Docker SDK (not in code)\n100: - Support `registry_url` parameter for non-Docker-Hub registries\n101: \n102: ## Integration Points\n103: \n104: ### BuildRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n105: - Uses `build_image()` for local Docker builds\n106: - Uses `get_image_info()` after build to retrieve image metadata\n107: - Uses `remove_image()` for cleanup on build failure\n108: \n109: ### PublishRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n110: - Uses `push_image()` for publishing to registries\n111: - Uses `get_image_info()` for image metadata display\n112: - Passes registry credentials from metadata to push operation\n113: \n114: ### CLI Commands\n115: - Indirect usage via runtime classes (no direct CLI integration)\n116: - Errors propagated through runtime error handling\n117: - Verbose flag passed from CLI commands through runtimes\n118: \n119: ## Impact Analysis\n120: \n121: ### Positive Impacts\n122: \n123: 1. **Separation of concerns**: Docker operations isolated from business logic\n124: 2. **Testability**: Easy to mock Docker SDK for unit testing\n125: 3. **Maintainability**: Single source of truth for Docker operations\n126: 4. **Reusability**: Consistent Docker behavior across CLI commands\n127: 5. **Error handling**: Centralized, consistent error messages\n128: \n129: ### Breaking Changes\n130: \n131: None. This is a new service module that doesn't modify existing functionality.\n132: \n133: ### Dependencies\n134: \n135: - **New dependency**: `docker>=6.0.0` (Docker SDK for Python)\n136: - **Existing dependencies**: `pathlib`, `logging`, `typing`, `rich` (for logging integration)\n137: \n138: ### File Modifications\n139: \n140: 1. **New file**:\n141:    - `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`: Complete `DockerService` implementation\n142: \n143: 2. **Modified files**:\n144:    - `agentcube/services/__init__.py`: Add service docstring\n145:    - `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`: Use `DockerService` instead of direct SDK calls\n146:    - `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`: Use `DockerService` for push operations\n147: \n148: 3. **Configuration**:\n149:    - `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`: Add `docker>=6.0.0` to project dependencies\n150: \n151: ### Risk Assessment\n152: \n153: | Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n154: |------|------------|------------|\n155: | Docker SDK API changes | Low | Pin version to `docker>=6.0.0,<7.0.0` |\n156: | Registry authentication failures | Medium | Comprehensive error messages, retry logic |\n157: | Build log streaming issues | Low | Test with various Dockerfile scenarios |\n158: | Proxy build_args handling | Medium | Validate build_args format before use |\n159: \n160: ## Alternatives Considered\n161: \n162: ### Alternative 1: Direct Docker CLI integration\n163: \n164: **Approach**: Use `subprocess` to call `docker build`, `docker push`, etc.\n165: \n166: **Rejected because**:\n167: - Requires parsing CLI output instead of structured data\n168: - Less portable across operating systems\n169: - No native Python error handling\n170: - Harder to test\n171: \n172: ### Alternative 2: No abstraction layer\n173: \n174: **Approach**: Directly import and use Docker SDK in runtime classes\n175: \n176: **Rejected because**:\n177: - Duplicates Docker initialization logic\n178: - Inconsistent error handling across runtimes\n179: - Harder to mock for testing\n180: - Mixes concerns (Docker operations vs agent lifecycle)\n181: \n182: ### Alternative 3: Third-party Docker wrapper\n183: \n184: **Approach**: Use existing Docker wrapper libraries\n185: \n186: **Rejected because**:\n187: - Adds unnecessary dependency\n188: - Existing libraries may not match CLI requirements\n189: - Custom implementation allows tighter integration with CLI features\n190: \n191: ## Acceptance Criteria\n192: \n193: ### Core Functionality\n194: \n195: - [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `True` when Docker daemon is running\n196: - [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `False` when Docker daemon is stopped\n197: - [ ] `build_image()` successfully builds images from Dockerfiles\n198: - [ ] `build_image()` streams build logs to console\n199: - [ ] `build_image()` supports build_args for proxy configuration\n200: - [ ] `get_image_info()` returns correct image metadata\n201: - [ ] `get_image_info()` formats size in human-readable format\n202: - [ ] `push_image()` successfully pushes to Docker Hub with credentials\n203: - [ ] `push_image()` handles registry URL retagging\n204: - [ ] `remove_image()` removes images successfully\n205: - [ ] `remove_image()` returns `False` on failure and logs warning\n206: \n207: ### Error Handling\n208: \n209: - [ ] Raises `RuntimeError` when Docker is unavailable\n210: - [ ] Raises appropriate exceptions for build failures\n211: - [ ] Handles authentication failures gracefully\n212: - [ ] Logs detailed errors in verbose mode\n213: - [ ] Provides user-friendly error messages\n214: \n215: ### Integration\n216: \n217: - [ ] BuildRuntime successfully uses DockerService for local builds\n218: - [ ] PublishRuntime successfully uses DockerService for publishing\n219: - [ ] Verbose flag is respected for logging\n220: - [ ] Errors propagate correctly through runtime classes\n221: \n222: ### Testing\n223: \n224: - [ ] Unit tests for all public methods\n225: - [ ] Mock Docker SDK for testing without Docker daemon\n226: - [ ] Integration tests with real Docker daemon\n227: - [ ] Test proxy configuration via build_args\n228: - [ ] Test registry authentication and push\n229: \n230: ## Implementation Timeline\n231: \n232: Estimated effort: **3-4 days**\n233: \n234: | Phase | Duration | Deliverables |\n235: |-------|----------|--------------|\n236: | Phase 1: Core implementation | 1.5 days | `DockerService` class with all methods |\n237: | Phase 2: Error handling and logging | 0.5 day | Comprehensive error handling, verbose logging |\n238: | Phase 3: Runtime integration | 0.5 day | Update BuildRuntime and PublishRuntime |\n239: | Phase 4: Testing | 1 day | Unit tests, integration tests |\n240: | Phase 5: Documentation | 0.5 day | Docstrings, examples, pyproject.toml update |\n241: \n242: ## References\n243: \n244: - CLI Toolkit Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` (lines 216-243)\n245: - CLI Specification: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` (Requirements 547-563 for Docker integration)\n246: - Docker SDK Documentation: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n247: - BuildRuntime: `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n248: - PublishRuntime: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n\n(End of file - total 248 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal describes the design and implementation of `DockerService` as a core service module within the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The service provides a Pythonic abstraction layer over Docker SDK operations required by the CLI's `pack`, `build`, and `publish` workflows.\n\n## Scope\n\n### DockerService Class (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n\nThe `DockerService` class will encapsulate all Docker SDK interactions:\n\n- **Docker availability check**: Verify Docker daemon is running and accessible\n- **Image building**: Build container images from Dockerfiles with optional build arguments\n- **Image information retrieval**: Query image metadata (ID, size, creation time)\n- **Image pushing**: Authenticate and push images to container registries\n- **Image removal**: Clean up local images with graceful error handling\n\n**Class interface**:\n```python","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871253193,"end":1775871253228}}}}
